      <scopecontent id="aspace_9a3df92f099ffd90aa87af586b899a21">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The material consists of scrapbooks of Karl Parrish, Class of 1934, School of Engineering, Yale University, documenting the Yale campus and downtown New Haven, Connecticut. The scapbooks contain photographs, newsclippings, and a critique advocating the "greening" of Yale campus with the conversion of streets to walkways.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
